<section id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center fade-in">
      <h2 class="section-title">What this day is</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        The EBiM Benchmark is a globally coordinated benchmark for real-world embodied bimanual manipulation, with cross-continent real-robot validation at partner labs in Hamburg, Munich, Pittsburgh, and Shanghai. The Hamburg Open Day opens that work up to the wider community for a day — the tasks, the evaluation protocol, the hardware, and the people running it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="who-grid fade-in">
      <div class="who-card">
        <h3>Researchers &amp; students</h3>
        <p>Manipulation, robot learning, VLA and foundation models, HRI — anyone who cares whether benchmark numbers survive contact with a real robot.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="who-card">
        <h3>IJCAI-ECAI 2026 attendees</h3>
        <p>Bremen to Hamburg is about an hour by train. A block of seats is reserved for IJCAI-ECAI attendees — but registration closes on 14 August, before the conference opens, so book your seat before you travel.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="who-card">
        <h3>Industry &amp; partners</h3>
        <p>See the standardized platform and the evaluation setup that four testbeds are running in parallel.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="od-callout fade-in">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
           stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
